-- Kazakhstan to widen tenge's corridor to 185 tenge plus 3/minus 15 to dollar
-- By Mariya Gordeyeva
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 02:18AM EDT
-- None



ALMATY, Sept 3 (Reuters) - Kazakhstan plans to widen the tenge's trading corridor against the U.S. dollar to 185 tenge plus 3/minus 15, the head of the Kazakh central bank Kairat Kelimbetov told reporters on Wednesday.

"We plan to take this decision this week," he said.  The current corridor stands at 185 plus/minus 3 per dollar.